enableCashGroup(uint16,address,(uint8,ui.notice: Enables a cash group on a given currency so that it can have lend and borrow markets. Will also deploy an nToken contract so that markets can be initialized.

params.assetRateOracle: address of the rate oracle for converting interest bearing assets to underlying values
params.currencyId: id of the currency to enable
params.underlyingName: underlying token name for seeding nToken name
params.underlyingSymbol: underlying token symbol for seeding nToken symbol (i.e. nDAI)

listCurrency((address,bool,uint8,uint8,u.notice: Lists a new currency along with its exchange rate to ETH

params.assetToken: the token parameters for the asset token
params.buffer: multiplier (>= 100) for negative balances when calculating free collateral
params.haircut: multiplier (<= 100) for positive balances when calculating free collateral
params.liquidationDiscount: multiplier (>= 100) for exchange rate when liquidating
params.mustInvert: if the rate from the oracle needs to be inverted
params.underlyingToken: the underlying token (if asset token is an interest bearing wrapper)

setPauseRouterAndGuardian(address,addres.notice: Sets a new pause router and guardian address.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.rateOracle: new rate oracle for the asset

updateAuthorizedCallbackContract(address.notice: Approves contracts that can call `batchTradeActionWithCallback`. These contracts can "flash loan" from Notional V2 and receive a callback before the free collateral check. Flash loans via the Notional V2 liquidity pool are not very gas efficient so this is not generally available, it can be used for migrating borrows into Notional V2 from other platforms.

params.approved: true if the contract is authorized

params.cashGroup: new parameters for the cash group
params.currencyId: id of the currency to enable

updateDepositParameters(uint16,uint32[],.notice: Updates the deposit parameters for an nToken

params.currencyId: the currency id that the nToken references
params.depositShares: an array of values that represent the proportion of each deposit that will go to a respective market, must add up to DEPOSIT_PERCENT_BASIS. For example, 0.40e8, 0.40e8 and 0.20e8 will result in 40%, 40% and 20% deposited as liquidity into the 3 month, 6 month and 1 year markets.
params.leverageThresholds: an array of values denominated in RATE_PRECISION that mark the highest proportion of fCash where the nToken will provide liquidity. Above this proportion, the nToken will lend to the market instead to reduce the leverage in the market.

updateETHRate(uint16,address,bool,uint8,.notice: Updates ETH exchange rate or related parameters

params.buffer: multiplier (>= 100) for negative balances when calculating free collateral
params.haircut: multiplier (<= 100) for positive balances when calculating free collateral
params.liquidationDiscount: multiplier (>= 100) for exchange rate when liquidating
params.mustInvert: if the rate from the oracle needs to be inverted

updateGlobalTransferOperator(address,boo.notice: Sets a global transfer operator that can do authenticated ERC1155 transfers. This enables OTC trading or other use cases such as layer 2 authenticated transfers.

params.approved: true if the operator is allowed to transfer globally

updateIncentiveEmissionRate(uint16,uint3.notice: Updates the emission rate of incentives for a given currency

params.currencyId: the currency id that the nToken references
params.newEmissionRate: Target total incentives to emit for an nToken over an entire year denominated in WHOLE TOKENS (i.e. setting this to 1 means 1e8 tokens). The rate will not be exact due to multiplier effects and fluctuating token supply.

updateInitializationParameters(uint16,ui.notice: Updates the market initialization parameters for an nToken

params.annualizedAnchorRates: is a target interest rate that will be used to calculate a  rate anchor during initialize markets. This rate anchor will set the offset from the x-axis where the liquidity curve will be initialized. This is used in combination with previous market rates to determine the initial proportion where markets will be initialized every quarter.
params.currencyId: the currency id that the nToken references
params.proportions: used to combination with annualizedAnchorRate set the initial proportion when a market is first initialized. This is required since there is no previous rate to reference.

updateMaxCollateralBalance(uint16,uint72.notice: Sets a maximum balance on a given currency. Max collateral balance cannot be set on a currency that is actively used in trading, this may cause issues with liquidation. Also, max collateral balance is only set on asset tokens (not underlying tokens) because underlying tokens are not held as contract balances.

params.currencyId: id of the currency to set the max collateral balance on
params.maxCollateralBalanceInternalPrecision: amount of collateral balance that can be held in this currency denominated in internal token precision

updateTokenCollateralParameters(uint16,u.notice: Updates collateralization parameters for an nToken

params.cashWithholdingBuffer10BPS: nToken residuals may be negative fCash (debt), in this case cash is withheld to transfer to accounts that take on the debt. This parameter denominates the discounted rate at which the cash will be withheld at for this purpose.
params.currencyId: the currency id that the nToken references
params.liquidationHaircutPercentage: a percentage of nToken present value (> pvHaircutPercentage and <= 100) at which liquidators will purchase nTokens during liquidation
params.pvHaircutPercentage: a percentage (< 100) that the present value of the nToken's assets will be valued at for the purposes of free collateral, relevant when accounts hold nTokens as collateral against debts.
params.residualPurchaseIncentive10BPS: nTokens will have residual amounts of fCash at the end of each quarter that are "dead weight" because they are at idiosyncratic maturities and do not contribute to actively providing liquidity. This parameter will incentivize market participants to purchase these residuals at a discount from the on chain oracle rate, denominated in 10 basis point increments. These residuals will be added back into nToken balances and will be used to provide liquidity upon the next market initialization.
params.residualPurchaseTimeBufferHours: an arbitrage opportunity is available by pushing markets in one direction before quarterly settlement to generate large residual balances that can be purchased at a discount. The time buffer here ensures that anyone attempting such an act would have to wait some number of hours (likely a few days) before they could attempt to purchase residuals, ensuring that the market could realign to rates where the arbitrage is no longer possible.
